comments: It was quite interesting. I feel like I trained my memory while working on it. As well as my color recognition skills.
strategy: No strategy in particular, I just moved the slider until the object looked similar to the one I remember in terms of color. I tried not to focus on the individual shades too much and instead relied on my memory. I did assign each of the two objects a rough color during the brief moment I saw them (pink elephant, orange bench and etc), which made it easier not to get the color of the two confused.
